The Chronicle Sikhumbuzo Moyo, Senior Sports Reporter FANS who will come to Barbourfields Stadium on Sunday will pay half  of the entry fees  if they pay using One Money after mobile communications giant NetOne undertook to pay the other difference. Highlanders and Caps United, who clash at Emgumeni, are both sponsored by NetOne. Gate charges for the blockbuster encounter have been pegged at $5 for the rest of the ground, $10 Wings and $20 VIP. “Good news from the #TheoneTheOnly! Get your ticket for half the price when you pay using using @OneMoneyZW for the @HighlandersBosso and @capsunitedfczw match,” Netone  announced through their official Twitter account. More details to follow……